### Feature: REP Offsets in DP (greedy pre-pass)

#### Approach
Added a greedy forward pre-pass (before the DP loop) that simulates the LRU rep[]
cache and records where REP matches are available. Stored in rep_match[i].
The DP backward pass adds choice=3 (use rep_match[i]) with ovhd_rep overhead —
much cheaper than EXACT (token+1B len = 2 param bytes vs 3-5 for EXACT variants).
ovhd_rep is computed from pass-1 REP token frequencies: -log2(rep_cnt/total) + 2×h_tok.
Forward trace handles choice=3 identically to other exact matches, with fallback
to EXACT if the actual rep[] state diverged from the pre-pass estimate.

#### Result
  ntdll.dll    : 0.4819  (no change)
  kernel32.dll : 0.4793  (−0.01 pt)
  user32.dll   : 0.3914  (−0.01 pt)

Essentially neutral. The greedy pre-pass estimate diverges from the DP's actual
parse choices, so many predicted REP positions fall back to EXACT in the trace.
Same root cause as the previous REP blending regression — accurate REP prediction
requires knowing the full parse, which is circular. Change kept (tiny positive,
no regression) but limits of the approach now documented.

