### Feature: Separated Opcode + Parameter Streams → ZXL6

#### Problem
ZXL5 encoded opcode bytes and parameter bytes (offsets, lengths, mtype, delta) into a
single interleaved stream with one shared rANS model. The two have radically different
distributions: opcode bytes are sparse (mostly 0x00-0xF6 literal-run values plus a few
0xF7-0xFF match opcodes); parameter bytes are heavily biased toward small values (offsets
0-255 dominate via EXACT1, lengths almost always 0-20). A shared frequency table is a
poor model for both simultaneously.

#### Solution
Split the token stream into two independent streams:
  opcode_buf — one byte per event: the match/lit-run token type (0x00–0xFF)
  param_buf  — all match parameters concatenated: offset bytes, length bytes, mtype, delta

Each gets its own rANS frequency table and is encoded/decoded as an independent stream.
The decompressor reads the token opcode, then consumes the correct number of bytes from
the param stream based on the opcode's parameter count.

#### Header Changes (ZXL5 → ZXL6)
Magic: 0x354C585A → 0x364C585A
Header now 7 uint32 fields (was 5) + opcode_freq_table + param_freq_table + lit tables.

Old: [uncomp][enc_tok][lit_total][tok_dec_len][lit_dec_len][tok_freqs][lit_freqs]...
New: [uncomp][enc_opcode][enc_param][lit_total][opcode_dec_len][param_dec_len][lit_dec_len]
     [opcode_freqs][param_freqs][lit_freqs]...

Header overhead increase: +520 bytes/block. At 512KB blocks this is 0.001% — negligible.

#### DP Overhead Formula Change
Old: OVHD(tok, nparams) = -log2(count[tok] / total_tokens) + nparams × h_tok
New: OVHD(tok, nparams) = -log2(count[tok] / total_opcodes) + nparams × h_param

h_param = entropy of param stream = average bits per param byte under the param rANS model.
This is more accurate: opcode cost comes from opcode entropy, param byte cost from param entropy.
For REP matches: overhead = opcode cost + 1 × h_param (1 param byte = 1B length).

